No hay nada que esconder, yo ando totalmente legal
Jefe, yo soy cantante, yo vengo de trabajar

Y aunque digan que soy

BUuhWIiNnx4.title: Farruko - Helicóptero (Live Session) | Vevo Ctrl
BUuhWIiNnx4.description:
Farruko - Helicóptero - Live Session | Vevo Ctrl 

Been to the club or a workout class lately? Then you’ve probably heard “Pepas,” the party anthem that turned Farruko into a crossover star. And guess what? “Pepas” wasn’t the only hit on the Puerto Rican singer/rapper's acclaimed ‘La 167’ album. “La Toxica” - especially the remix with Myke Towers and Sech - was a highly successful return to his reggaeton roots. The album's “El Incomprendido” plays with the feisty guaracha style, which blends traditional elements of cumbia and regional Mexican with pulsing EDM arrangements. Farruko and his pal DJ Adoni couldn't stop dancing when they hit our Ctrl studios. Farruko kept the energy whirring on “Helicóptero,” too. No question, both are infectious blasts of energy.

Watch the “Pepas” video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=y8trd3gjJt0

hBE5_dVBC_0.title: Farruko, Dj Adoni - El Incomprendido (Live Session) | Vevo Ctrl
hBE5_dVBC_0.description:
Farruko - El Incomprendido - Live Session | Vevo Ctrl 

Been to the club or a workout class lately? Then you’ve probably heard “Pepas,” the party anthem that turned Farruko into a crossover star. And guess what? “Pepas” wasn’t the only hit on the Puerto Rican singer/rapper's acclaimed ‘La 167’ album. “La Toxica” - especially the remix with Myke Towers and Sech - was a highly successful return to his reggaeton roots. The album's “El Incomprendido” plays with the feisty guaracha style, which blends traditional elements of cumbia and regional Mexican with pulsing EDM arrangements. Farruko and his pal DJ Adoni couldn't stop dancing when they hit our Ctrl studios. Farruko kept the energy whirring on “Helicóptero,” too. No question, both are infectious blasts of energy.

Watch the “Pepas” video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=y8trd3gjJt0
